CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper March 29, 1958, pg. 8, reads: "Attention State Liquor Control Board - How Many More Taverns Can Homewood-Brushton Stand?  One of '11 in Five' - One of the 11 liquor dispensing establishments within a five-block area on Frankstown Ave., is Kraemer's [Kramer's] Tavern in the 7300 block of Frankstown Ave.... - All Photos by Harris."
TitMainTitle: Men working with rubble on sidewalk, with Kramer's Cafe in background, 7300 block of Frankstown Avenue and Sterrett Street, Homewood
